**Explanation:**  
These 20 apps were selected and ranked primarily by their **user engagement**, based on metrics such as subscriber count, content library size, original content investment, interactive features, and user-friendly design noted in multiple sources. Netflix leads due to its massive library, personalized recommendations, and original content exclusives, ensuring high engagement[1][2][3]. Amazon Prime Video and Disney+ follow closely, given their extensive content and subscriber base[1][2][4]. Hulu and HBO Max also rank highly owing to their strong original programming and diverse offerings[2][4]. Plex is noted for its customizable and flexible user experience, positively impacting engagement[1]. Other notable streaming services like BBC iPlayer, ITVX, Channel 4, and My5 show strong growth and user engagement in their regional markets[3]. Additional globally popular and niche platforms such as Apple TV+, Kick (live broadcasting), Paramount+, YouTube Premium, and free tier services like Tubi and Peacock add to the list based on broad user interaction and content variety[2][4]. Specialty platforms like Crunchyroll (anime), Shudder (horror), Discovery+ (documentaries), and Sling TV (live TV integration) also contribute to high engagement within their focus areas and user communities.